Tag colors are a great idea, especially when combined with filters to set the tags. 

BUT - if I tag something with two tags, then it takes the color of the first (alphabetically I think). This makes sense if BOTH have colors, but if I have for example &quot;call&quot; and &quot;project1&quot; and &quot;project2&quot;  and pick green for Project 1 and red for &quot;Project2&quot;, then I really don&apos;t want those colors to disappear if I also tag it with &quot;call&quot; which has no color specified. 


Reproducible: Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1.Create a tag MMMM with color Red
2.Create a tag AAAA - don&apos;t set a color
3. Tag something MMMM - it changes to red
4. Tag same item AAAA - the color disappears (defaults to black).
I think it should stay red.</thetext>
